Sentencas: Density functional theory was used to design a non-noble metal catalyst for low temperature oxygen reduction.
Titulo: Nonprecious Metal Catalysts for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: A core-shell catalyst of Ag vertical bar Ag(x)Cu(5-x)Zn(8) was found to have an electronic structure predicted to be near optimal for weak oxygen bonding, and the activation energy for dissociation was low.
Titulo: Nonprecious Metal Catalysts for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This catalyst was made via evaporation and sputtering and tested as the anode and cathode of low temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Nonprecious Metal Catalysts for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The new catalyst showed charge transfer resistance 16 times higher than platinum on the cathode side, and five times lower on the anode side at 400 degrees C.
Titulo: Nonprecious Metal Catalysts for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The resistance to common catalyst poisons CO and H(2)S is enhanced compared to Pt.
Titulo: Nonprecious Metal Catalysts for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Further, the catalyst was tested as the cathode of a proton exchange membrane fuel cell by testing the half cell reaction in a rotating disk electrode.
Titulo: Nonprecious Metal Catalysts for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The exchange current density was within a factor of 3 lower than Pt, while the charge transfer coefficient was a factor of 3 higher than Pt.
Titulo: Nonprecious Metal Catalysts for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The Ag vertical bar Ag(x)Cu(5-x)Zn(8) catalyst is a promising start to develop non-noble metal catalysts.
Titulo: Nonprecious Metal Catalysts for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
